HEADWORD: Depopulation
<hw>De*pop`u*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>depopulatio</ets> pillaging: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧population</ets>
depopulation.]</ety> <def>The act of depopulating, or condition of being
depopulated; destruction or expulsion of inhabitants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The desolation and <qex>depopulation</qex> [of St.Quentin] were
now complete.</q> <rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Depopulator</ent>⟦br⟧
